This section retrieves useful data from the information gathered from users.
The data is expressed in a visually more understanding manner.
In other words, the information from user stories is used to create a use case diagram.
The transition from user stories to a use case diagram involves: 
  i. The identification of actors from user roles
 ii. The extraction of system functionalities from the actions described in each story
iii. Modelling the interactions and relationships between the actors and the use cases
 iv. Setting the system boundary

